HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 334
By Raper
A RESOLUTION to commend and congratulate Mitch Cochran on
the occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to honor those worthy
professionals who have served with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
careers; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Mitch Cochran, who has distinguished himself as a
public-spirited citizen of the highest order and as an exceptional asset to this State; and
WHEREAS, after an illustrious career of over half a century in the food industry, Mr.
Cochran is taking his much-deserved retirement, marking the end of an era that has shaped
both the Cleveland community and Food City, the company he has so ably served; and
WHEREAS, Mitch Cochran's career began in 1972 with Red Food Stores, where he
bagged groceries; over the years, through sheer determination, a strong work ethic, and a
relentless commitment to excellence, he worked his way through the ranks, taking on roles such
as dairy manager, assistant store manager, and, ultimately, store manager; and
WHEREAS, for the past three decades, Mr. Cochran has been the cornerstone of the
McGrady Drive Food City in Cleveland, where his leadership and passion for service have made
a profound impact on both his team and the community; and
WHEREAS, his dedication to his job is evidenced by the strong relationships he has built
with countless customers and teammates over the years; he has not only shaped the store into
a success but has nurtured the growth of many individuals who have gone on to become
supervisors, store managers, district managers, and even executive vice president; and
