WHEREAS, Mitch Cochran's legacy as a mentor and a developer of talent is woven into
the very fabric of Food City, and his infectious personality and generous spirit have made him a
beloved figure in Cleveland; and
WHEREAS, known for never meeting a stranger, he is always ready to lend a hand,
offer a listening ear, or share advice borne of his extensive experience; his ability to make
everyone feel like family has earned him the admiration and respect of all who cross his path;
and
WHEREAS, throughout his many professional accomplishments, Mr. Cochran has
enjoyed the love and support of his dear wife, Marcia; daughter, Stephanie; and granddaughter,
Kaylee, all of whom bring him endless joy and fulfillment; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Mr. Cochran for his
dedication to his industry as well as the State of Tennessee and its citizens; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commend and congratulate Mitch Cochran upon the occasion of his
retirement, applauding his dedication to excellence and extending to him our best wishes for
every future success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
